b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both DeepL and Weglot share a solid foundation of core features including Machine Translation, Glossary, Api Access, Team Collaboration. Where DeepL pulls ahead is with exclusive access to File Formats, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Weglot uniquely offers Cms Integration, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, DeepL holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 10/10, while Weglot scores 8/10 overall and 10/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, DeepL offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Weglot's starting price of $15/mo. DeepL has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Weglot does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
