f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. DeepL is best suited for businesses, translators, content teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Weglot, meanwhile, shines for website owners, e commerce, WordPress users, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, DeepL describes itself as \"AI-powered translation tool renowned for natural and accurate translations.\" Weglot, established in 2016, positions itself as \"Website translation solution with automatic detection and multilingual SEO.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **DeepL** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 8.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Weglot is a poor choice — far from it. Weglot excels in its own right, particularly for website owners and e commerce.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best translation quality for european languages, go with DeepL. If easiest website translation setup matters more to you, Weglot is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
